  "prompt_type": "cognitive",
  "prompt_text": "Explain how DNS resolution works, step by step, from typing a URL to receiving a response.",
  "response_text": "DNS resolution is the process of translating a domain name into an IP address that computers use to communicate with each other over the internet. Here’s a step-by-step explanation of how DNS resolution works from typing a URL to receiving a response:\n\n1. **User Input**: A user types a URL (e.g., www.example.com) into their web browser.\n\n2. **Local DNS Cache Check**: The web browser checks its local DNS cache to see if it already has the IP address for \"www.example.com\". If the IP address is found in the cache, the browser uses that IP address and skips the rest of the steps.\n\n3. **Operating System DNS Cache Check**: If the IP address is not in the browser's cache, the request is passed to the operating system's DNS resolver. The resolver also checks its own cache to see if it has the IP address for \"www.example.com\".\n\n4. **Recursive Query to Root Nameserver**: If the IP address is not found in either cache, the resolver sends a recursive query to a root nameserver. The root nameserver does not have the final answer but knows which top-level domain (TLD) nameservers (like .com, .org, etc.) to contact next.\n\n5. **Query to TLD Nameserver**: The root nameserver responds with the IP address of the appropriate TLD nameserver (e.g., the .com nameserver). The resolver then queries this TLD nameserver.\n\n6. **Query to Authoritative Nameserver**: The TLD nameserver provides the IP address of the authoritative nameserver for \"example.com\". The resolver then queries this authoritative nameserver.\n\n7. **Response with IP Address**: The authoritative nameserver returns the IP address associated with \"www.example.com\" to the resolver.\n\n8. **Resolver Returns IP Address**: The resolver passes the IP address back to the web browser.\n\n9. **Web Browser Connects to Server**: The web browser uses the IP address to establish a connection with the server hosting \"www.example.com\" and begins loading the requested webpage.\n\n10. **Webpage Loading**: Once connected, the web browser can start downloading and rendering the webpage.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 10\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
